@node General "DayDream BBS - General Information"

General information
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
DayDream BBS was originally  developed for the IBM PC and it was some kind
of a QuickBBS clone.  It was programmed by Tuomas Tonteri.  When the A1200
was released Tuomas sold his PC and bought an Amiga.  He started to code a
new  AmiExpress-lookalike  BBS-program,  but   the  name  was   the  same,
DayDream  BBS.   At  the  beginning,  DayDream evolved rather rapidly, but
after  one year of programming Tuomas ran out of time and the studying and
his  girlfriend  took  all  his time, so he gave the sources etc to Hydra.
Soon  Tuomas changed back to the PC, but still DayDream is evolved at full
speed. After some time, Hydra felt that he was running out of inspiration,
and thought he wanted to move on to another platform. So he bought himself
A  PC  (yiks!)  and  started  running  Linux,  and also started to develop
DayDream  for  that  perticular OS.  He didn't want DayDream to die on the
Amiga, and started looking for a new developer for the Amiga OS version.
So..   Mattias ran into him and agreed to take over the development 
immedietly,  after all he was already a DayDream junkie at the time.  :)

After Mattias got some private problems, I as an DayDream junkie takeover
it (again) and I hope that I'll do it for a looonnnggg  time.


Any inquiries about the Linux version (and other OS versions exept for the
Amiga one) should go directly to Hydra.  His email is hydra@freenet.hut.fi

@endnode


@node Legal "DayDream BBS - Legal Info"

Legal Info
~~~~~~~~~~
I'm  not  responsible if DayDream causes any damage to your system.  You use it
at your own risk.

If  you  find  any bugs please inform me.  Also, if you have a MMU, try to find
enforcer hits and tell me where they (the hits) occur.

!NOTICE THIS!
If  you used cracked version of DayDream BBS please think about registering.
DayDream BBS is a result of years of hard work.  

I removed old protection checks in a hope that more people will be interested
in DayDream. This version is FREE, but all future releases will be protected 
again.




@{b}reqtools.library@{ub} is Copyright by Nico Francois.

DayDream uses MD5C.C by RSA Data Security, Inc. (MD5 message-digest algorithm)
@{b}Copyright (C) 1991-2, RSA Data Security, Inc. Created 1991. All rights reserved.@{ub}

@endnode


