@node GenInfo "DayDream BBS - General Information"

General information
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Configuration   of  DayDream  BBS  is  done  via  external  configprogram,
DreamConfig.   It  compilies  specified ascii file to the datafiles,  that
can be found in DayDream:Data/-directory.  Be sure you have correct number
of  lines  in each entry, or the DreamConfig will fail.  Compiler is quite
fast, it takes only few seconds to compile all data-files.

The basic configfile is included in distribution archive, just look at the
examples to get the idea.

From DD 1.21, MUI-Based config program is included. Before using it first
time, you'll need to compile DayDream.CFG, then you won't need DreamConfig
anymore if you want to continue using MUI-Config.

@endnode

@node MainConfig "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration"

4-2 - Main Configuration
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Main configuration in DayDream.CFG looks like this:

Note that MUI-Config widgets are not documented, but they are basicilly
the same as described below, so the stuff below is fairly useful even if
you are using MUI-Config.

!DAYDREAM.DAT
@{" BBSNAME...... " Link BBSNAME} My BBS
@{" SYSOP........ " Link SYSOP} Me
@{" LOCALUPLDPATH " Link LOCALUPLDPATH} Dh1:download/
@{" CHATDLPATH... " Link CHATDLPATH} dh1:download/
@{" OP_DMODE..... " Link OP_DMODE} 1
@{" SYSTEM_PW.... " Link SYSTEM_PW} -
@{" NEWUSER_PW... " Link NEWUSER_PW} -
@{" USERED_PW.... " Link USERED_PW} -
@{" FSCAN_BUFFER. " Link FSCAN_BUFFER} 60
@{" NEW_PRESET... " Link NEW_PRESET} 1
@{" IDLE......... " Link IDLE} 180
@{" AUTOCONF..... " Link AUTOCONF} 1
@{" FREEFORUL.... " Link FREEFORUL} 2000000
@{" ASK_REASON... " Link ASK_REASON} Y
@{" NAMEMODE..... " Link NAMEMODE} H
@{" LOCATION..... " Link LOCATION} O
@{" DISABLEWILDS. " Link DISABLEWILDS} N
@{" QUESTIONS.... " Link QUESTIONS} N
@{" LOGDISA...... " Link LOGDISA} Y
@{" QUICKLINEED.. " Link QUICKLINEED} N
@{" ASKHANDLE1ST. " Link ASKHANDLE1ST} N
@{" SYSOP_COL.... " Link SYSOP_COL} [36m
@{" USER_COL..... " Link USER_COL} [35m
@{" SHELL_PW..... " Link SHELL_PW} SODOM
@{" ALIENS....... " Link ALIENS} DayDream:Aliens/
@{" LINEEDCOM.... " Link LINEEDCOM} $
@{" FSED......... " Link FSED} Doors:FSEd %N
@{" CHATMODE..... " Link CHATMODE } S
@{" LOCALSCREEN.. " Link LOCALSCREEN } 30
@{" FREEDLLINE... " Link FREEDLLINE } [-] FREE DOWNLOAD <><><><> FREE DOWNLOAD [-]
@{" OLMPATH...... " Link OLMPATH} t:
@{" COSYSOPACCESS " Link COSYSOPACCESS} 250
@{" CONTROLCHAR.. " Link CONTROLCHAR} 255
@{" HOMEDIRS..... " Link HOMEDIRS} users:
@{" GROUPID...... " Link GROUPID} 99
@{" 1STUSERID.... " Link 1STUSERID} 20000
@{" CHATCMD...... " Link CHATCMD} Doors:fishchat %N
@{" COPYBUFFER... " Link COPYBUFFER} 200000
@{" DEF_HIDECURSO " Link DEF_HIDECURSO} N
@{" DEF_USECSI... " Link DEF_USECSI} N
@{" DEF_EXPERT... " Link DEF_EXPERT} N
@{" DEF_MAILSCAN. " Link DEF_MAILSCAN} Y
@{" DEF_NEWFILESC " Link DEF_NEWFILESC} N
@{" DEF_ALLOWNODE " Link DEF_ALLOWNODE} Y
@{" DEF_CLSINLIST " Link DEF_CLSINLIST} Y
@{" DEF_BGCHECK.. " Link DEF_BGCHECK} Y
~

@endnode

@node BBSNAME "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - BBSNAME"

BBSNAME...... 

      The actual name of your BBS.

@endnode

@node SYSOP "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - SYSOP"

SYSOP........ 

      Your name/handle.

@endnode

@node LOCALUPLDPATH "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - LOCALUPLDPATH"

LOCALUPLDPATH 

      Default path used for sending ascii files while in chat mode,
      for local uploading etc..

@endnode

@node CHATDLPATH "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - CHATDLPATH"

CHATDLPATH... 

      Path of directory where the files downloaded during a chat will be
      placed.

@endnode

@node OP_DMODE "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - OP_DMODE"

OP_DMODE..... 

      Display mode used to run "daydream n? lo" -connections in.

@endnode

@node SYSTEM_PW "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - SYSTEM_PW"

SYSTEM_PW.... 

      System password (- for none).

@endnode

@node NEWUSER_PW "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - NEWUSER_PW"

NEWUSER_PW... 

      New user password (- for none)

@endnode

@node USERED_PW "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - USERED_PW"

USERED_PW.... 

      Password required to  enter user editor.  To enter usereditor,  user
      also requires the privilege flag of UserEditor to be set as On.

@endnode

@node FSCAN_BUFFER "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - FSCAN_BUFFER"

FSCAN_BUFFER. 

      Size of buffer (kb) used by  Zippy Search, File  scan  and New files
      scan.

@endnode

@node NEW_PRESET "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - NEW_PRESET"

NEW_PRESET... 

      Access preset used for new users.

@endnode

@node IDLE "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - IDLE"

IDLE......... 

      Inactivity  timeout  in seconds. If  nothing happens in the BBS  for
      this period of time, user will be disconnected.

@endnode

@node AUTOCONF "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - AUTOCONF"

AUTOCONF..... 

      Conference to join,  if user doesn't  have access  to the Conference
      where he was on when logged off last time (=autojoin conference)

@endnode

@node FREEFORUL "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - FREEFORUL"

FREEFORUL.... 

      Free  space  required  for uploads  in bytes.  Suggested value about
      2000000.

@endnode

@node ASK_REASON "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - ASK_REASON"

ASK_REASON... 

      Set wether or not user is asked for a reason when paging for a chat

@endnode

@node NAMEMODE "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - NAMEMODE"

NAMEMODE..... 

      If H, use handles in the BBS as default.
      If R, use real names in the BBS as default.

@endnode

@node LOCATION "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - LOCATION"

LOCATION..... 

      If L, use zip code as location.
      If O, use organization as location.

@endnode

@node DISABLEWILDS "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DISABLEWILDS"

DISABLEWILDS. 

      Set wether or not  wildcards can  be used  during  login. Be careful
      with  this, as a plain * can  be used to list  all the  handles  AND
      real names that are used in the board.

@endnode

@node QUESTIONS "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - QUESTIONS"

QUESTIONS.... 

      Y/N switch.  If this  is Y, DayDream  will run Questionnaire for the
      user if he  hasn't answered it yet. (If userbase was converted  from
      /X etc)

@endnode

@node LOGDISA "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - LOGDISA"

LOGDISA......

      Y/N switch. If this  is Y,  DayDream will  not write  logfile during
      a local operator login.

@endnode

@node QUICKLINEED "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - QUICKLINEED"

QUICKLINEED..

      Y/N switch. If this is Y,  CR in empty  line will enter command mode
      in line editor.

@endnode

@node ASKHANDLE1ST "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - ASKHANDLE1ST"

      Y/N switch. If this is Y,  Handle will be asked before real name when
      a user is about to create account.

@endnode

@node SYSOP_COL "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - SYSOP_COL"

SYSOP_COL.... 

      Ansicode that will be used for the sysop's colour in the chat mode.

@endnode

@node USER_COL "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - USER_COL"

USER_COL..... 

      Ansicode that will be used for the user's colour in the chat mode.

@endnode

@node SHELL_PW "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - SHELL_PW"

SHELL_PW..... 

      Password required for Remote shell operation (- for none)

@endnode

@node ALIENS "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - ALIENS"

ALIENS.......

      Path to place  files that are found  in Temporary directory when  it
      needs to be cleaned. There  can be files  eg. if system  has crashed 
      during uploading. If this is -, files in temporary directory will be
      deleted.

@endnode

@node LINEEDCOM "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - LINEEDCOM"

LINEEDCOM....

      Character that activates the command mode in line editor.

@endnode

@node FSED "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - FSED"

FSED.........

      Command to be executed to start FullScreen Editor or - if you don't
      want to have FullScreen Editor.

@endnode

@node CHATMODE "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - CHATMODE"

CHATMODE.....

      L = Line chat, S = Split screen chat, A = Ask, D = Door

@endnode

@node LOCALSCREEN "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - LOCALSCREEN"

LOCALSCREEN..

      The length of the local screen. 

@endnode

@node FREEDLLINE "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - FREEDLLINE"

FREEDLLINE...

      Line to be added after free downloads or -.

@endnode

@node OLMPATH "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - OLMPATH"

OLMPATH......

      Path to store multiline OLM's (Introduced in DD 1.17). If this is -,
      old-fashioned OLM's will be used. (OLM=OnLine message)

@endnode

@node COSYSOPACCESS "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - COSYSOPACCESS"

COSYSOPACCESS

      Access level of Co-SysOp. Currently this is used only in userlist and
      this should be always lower than 255.

@endnode

@node CONTROLCHAR "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - CONTROLCHAR"

CONTROLCHAR..

      Ascii code for control character in TXT files. Should be 255.

@endnode

@node CONTROLCHAR "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - CONTROLCHAR"

CONTROLCHAR..

      Ascii code for control character in TXT files. Should be 255.

@endnode

@node HOMEDIRS "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - HOMEDIRS"

HOMEDIRS......

      Path for home directories for users. Use - if you haven't offered
      possiblity for FTP transfers.

@endnode

@node GROUPID "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - GROUPID"

GROUPID

      GID for ftp users. SHOULD be 99 (usually guest).

@endnode

@node 1STUSERID "Vittujoo"

1STUSERID

      UID Number of first ftp user (UID=1STUSERID+User->user_account_id)

@endnode

@node CHATCMD "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - CHATCMD"

CHATCMD

      Command to run, if SysOp wants to use external chatter. Must be
      DDDP door. Don't forget %n. If you don't have an external chatter,
      use -.

@endnode

@node COPYBUFFER "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - COPYBUFFER"

COPYBUFFER

       Size of copybuffer in bytes.. Bigger buffer will copy the
       file faster, but will eat more memory too.

@endnode

@node DEF_HIDECURSO "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DEF_HIDECURSO"

DEF_HIDECURSO

	New user default:
	Hide cursor in text files (Y/N)

@endnode

@node DEF_USECSI "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DEF_USECSI"

DEF_USECSI

	New user default:
	Use CSI codes instead of ANSI (Y/N)

@endnode

@node DEF_EXPERT "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DEF_EXPERT"

DEF_EXPERT

	New user default:
	Use expert mode (Y/N)

@endnode

@node DEF_MAILSCAN "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DEF_MAILSCAN"

DEF_MAILSCAN

	New user default:
	Mail scan at login (Y/N/A) (A=Ask)

@endnode

@node DEF_NEWFILESC "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DEF_NEWFILESC"

DEF_NEWFILESC

	New user default:
	New file scan at login (Y/N/A) (A=Ask)

@endnode

@node DEF_ALLOWNODE "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DEF_ALLOWNODE"

DEF_ALLOWNODE

	New user default:
	Allow node messages (Y/N)

@endnode

@node DEF_CLSINLIST "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DEF_CLSINLIST"

DEF_CLSINLIST

	New user default:
	CLS's in filelist (Y/N)

@endnode

@node DEF_BGCHECK "DayDream BBS - Main Configuration - DEF_BGCHECK"

DEF_BGCHECK

	New user default:
	Background file checker (Y/N)

@endnode

@node Confs "DayDream BBS - Conferences"

Conferences
~~~~~~~~~~~
@{" CONF_NUMB..... " Link CONF_NUMB} 1
@{" CONF_NAME..... " Link CONF_NAME} Example Conference
@{" CONF_PATH..... " Link CONF_PATH} DayDream:ExampleConf/
@{" CONF_FILEAREAS " Link CONF_FILEAREAS} 2
@{" CONF_UPLOADSTO " Link CONF_UPLOADSTO} 2
@{" CONF_MSGBASES. " Link CONF_MSGBASES} 2
@{" CONF_COMMENTS. " Link CONF_COMMENTS} 1
@{" CONF_ULPATH... " Link CONF_ULPATH} DayDream:ExampleConf/New/
@{" CONF_NSAREAS.. " Link CONF_NSAREAS} A
@{" CONF_DEFFSCAN. " Link CONF_DEFFSCAN} N
@{" CONF_FREELEECH " Link CONF_FREELEECH} N
@{" CONF_NOCREDS.. " Link CONF_NOCREDS} N
@{" CONF_SENTBY... " Link CONF_SENTBY} Y
@{" CONF_LONGNAMES " Link CONF_LONGNAMES} N
@{" CONF_ASKDEST.. " Link CONF_ASKDEST} N
@{" CONF_NOWILDS.. " Link CONF_NOWILDS} Y
@{" CONF_NOWILDFLG " Link CONF_NOWILDFLG} N
@{" CONF_NODUPECHK " Link CONF_NODUPECHK} N
@{" CONF_NOFILECHK " Link CONF_NOFILECHK} N
@{" CONF_NOREQ.... " Link CONF_NOREQ} N
@{" CONF_PASSWORD. " Link CONF_PASSWORD} -
+

The  next  line  specifies what to do next.  If it's +, then next block of
config  file  is  for  message base.  If it's *, then next block of config
file  is  for  a  new  conference  and  if  it's ~, it's  the  end  of the 
Conferences.DAT.

@{" BASE_NUMBER... " Link BASE_NUMBER} 1
@{" BASE_TYPE..... " Link BASE_TYPE} L
@{" BASE_LOWEST... " Link BASE_LOWEST} -
@{" BASE_HIGHEST.. " Link BASE_HIGHEST} -
@{" BASE_MAXMSGS.. " Link BASE_MAXMSGS} 1000
@{" BASE_NAME..... " Link BASE_NAME} Comments to SysOp
@{" BASE_FIDOTAG.. " Link BASE_FIDOTAG} -
@{" BASE_ORIGIN... " Link BASE_ORIGIN} -
@{" BASE_FIDOADD.. " Link BASE_FIDOADD} -
@{" BASE_ALLOWPBLC " Link BASE_ALLOWPBLC} N
@{" BASE_ALLOWPRIV " Link BASE_ALLOWPRIV} Y
@{" BASE_FILEATTAC " Link BASE_FILEATTAC} Y
@{" BASE_NAMES.... " Link BASE_NAMES} R
@{" BASE_ALL=EALL. " Link BASE_ALL=EALL} N
@{" BASE_QUOTE.... " Link BASE_QUOTE} L
@{" BASE_DEFGRAB.. " Link BASE_DEFGRAB} Y
~

The  next  line specifies what to do next.  If it's +, then the next block
of  config  file  is  for message base.  If it's *, then the next block of
config file is for  new conference  and if  it's  ~,  it's  the end of the
Conferences.DAT.

@endnode

@node CONF_NUMB "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_NUMB"

CONF_NUMB.....

      Conference Number. Allowed values are 1-64.

@endnode

@node CONF_NAME "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_NAME"

CONF_NAME.....

      Name of the conference.

@endnode

@node CONF_PATH "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_PATH"

CONF_PATH.....

      Path of the conference. End with / or :

@endnode

@node CONF_FILEAREAS "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_FILEAREAS"

CONF_FILEAREAS

      Number of fileareas in conference. Allowed values 0-255.

@endnode

@node CONF_UPLOADSTO "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_UPLOADSTO"

CONF_UPLOADSTO

      Number of area to place uploads in.

@endnode

@node CONF_MSGBASES "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_MSGBASES"

CONF_MSGBASES.

      Number of message bases. MUST be the same value as number of defined
      message bases or DD will piss.

@endnode

@node CONF_COMMENTS "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_COMMENTS"

CONF_COMMENTS.

      Number of message base to place comments in. If 0, comments won't be
      accepted in the conference.

@endnode

@node CONF_ULPATH "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_ULPATH"

CONF_ULPATH...

      Path of the directory  where uploads  are moved after  transfer. End
      with : or /.

@endnode

@node CONF_NSAREAS "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_NSAREAS"

CONF_NSAREAS..

      Arealist for  global  new file scan. Area list uses the same routine
      as N S [....]-menu command. [....] will be placed with this.

@endnode

@node CONF_DEFFSCAN "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_DEFFSCAN"

CONF_DEFFSCAN.

      If  you  want  this conference  to be  turned  on as default for the
      global file scan, use Y. If not, then N.

@endnode

@node CONF_FREELEECH "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_FREELEECH"

CONF_FREELEECH

      If you want that all file in the conference are free downloads,  set
      this as Y.

@endnode

@node CONF_NOCREDS "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_NOCREDS"

CONF_NOCREDS..

      If you want that users won't get credits from the files they upload,
      set this as Y.

@endnode

@node CONF_SENTBY "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_SENTBY"

CONF_SENTBY...

      If you want that sent-by lines are in use, set this as Y.

@endnode

@node CONF_LONGNAMES "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_LONGNAMES"

CONF_LONGNAMES

      Selects filelist format for this conference. If this is Y, 18
      characters long filenames are used. If this is N, MS-Dos filenames
      are used.

      If you want to convert 12 chars filelist to 18 chars filelist,
      use included DayDream:Utils/oldlist2newlist to do it.

      The lists look like this:

----------------------------------------------------------] 12 CHARS [---------
ACSDD110.LZX P---  273942 14.05.95   _________________________________________
                                     \ ____   /     /     / ____  ____/ _____/
                                   .--\/__/  /  /__/  /__/  ___\___  \___  \/-.
                                   |  / \   /  /  /  /  /   :   \  \  \  \  \ |
                                   | /__/__/_____/_____/_________\_____\_____\|
                                   | \  \  \     \     \         /     /  M@!/|
                                   `--\__\__\_____\_____\_______/_____/_____/-'
                                         DayDream BBS V1.10 (14 May 95)
                                     The fastest Amiga BBS Package supporting
                                     WWF, BlueWave, Hydra, XPR, ARexx, stdio, 
                                    Offline Checking, File_id.diz, FidoNet etc.
                                        The Main executable is 100% ASM!
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

----------------------------------------------------------] 18 CHARS [---------
DayDreamBBS110.lha P-  313k 140595   _________________________________________
                                     \ ____   /     /     / ____  ____/ _____/
                                   .--\/__/  /  /__/  /__/  ___\___  \___  \/-.
                                   |  / \   /  /  /  /  /   :   \  \  \  \  \ |
                                   | /__/__/_____/_____/_________\_____\_____\|
                                   | \  \  \     \     \         /     /  M@!/|
                                   `--\__\__\_____\_____\_______/_____/_____/-'
                                         DayDream BBS V1.10 (14 May 95)
                                     The fastest Amiga BBS Package supporting
                                     WWF, BlueWave, Hydra, XPR, ARexx, stdio, 
                                    Offline Checking, File_id.diz, FidoNet etc.
                                        The Main executable is 100% ASM!
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@endnode

@node CONF_ASKDEST "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_ASKDEST"

CONF_ASKDEST..

      If you want that user will be asked for filearea for his/her upload
      instead of placing it in upload directory, set this as Y.

@endnode

@node CONF_NOWILDS "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_NOWILDS"

CONF_NOWILDS..

      If you don't want filenames to contain wildcards, set this to Y.

@endnode

@node CONF_NOWILDFLG "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_NOWILDFLG"

CONF_NOWILDFLG

      To disable wildcard support for file flagging, set this to Y.
      Flagging with wildcards is pretty slow in CD-Rom conferences.

@endnode

@node CONF_NODUPECHK "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_NODUPECHK"

CONF_NODUPECHK

      If you want to disable dupechecking in this conference, set this
      to Y.

@endnode

@node CONF_NOFILECHK "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_NOFILECHK"

CONF_NOFILECHK

      If you want to disable filechecking in the conference, set this
      to Y. Useful for eg. private conferences.

@endnode

@node CONF_NOREQ "DayDream BBS - Conference - CONF_NOREQ"

      If you want to disable filerequesters (NOT A DOS DISK IN DRIVE CD0:)
      in the conf, set this to Y. Useful if you listen audio-cd's with your
      CD-Rom.

@endnode

@node CONF_PASSWORD "DayDream BBS - Conferences - CONF_PASSWORD"

CONF_PASSWORD. -

      Password required for the conference or -.

@endnode

@node BASE_NUMBER "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_NUMBER"

BASE_NUMBER...

      Number of the message base. Allowed values are 1-254.

@endnode

@node BASE_TYPE "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_TYPE"

BASE_TYPE.....

      Message  base  type.   L = Local, E = FidoNet Echomail, N = Fidonet
      netmail.

@endnode

@node BASE_LOWEST "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_LOWEST"

BASE_LOWEST...

      Number  of  the  lowest  message.  If -, value  will  be  taken from
      existing Conferences.DAT. This should always be -. If you have blown
      your message bases up, just use included fixbases-program.

@endnode

@node BASE_HIGHEST "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_HIGHEST"

BASE_HIGHEST..

      Number  of  the  highest  message.  If -, value  will  be taken from
      existing Conferences.DAT. This should always be -. If you have blown
      your message bases up, just use included fixbases-program.

@endnode

@node BASE_MAXMSGS "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_MAXMSGS"

BASE_MAXMSGS..

      Maximum   number  of  messages  allowed  in  this  base.   Not  yet
      supported, but I'll write a maintenance tool soon which autodeletes
      these etc.

@endnode

@node BASE_NAME "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_NAME"

BASE_NAME.....

      Name of the message base.

@endnode

@node BASE_FIDOTAG "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_FIDOTAG"

BASE_FIDOTAG..

      FidoNet tag for the message base.  Case sensitive.  Use - if none.

@endnode

@node BASE_ORIGIN "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_ORIGIN"

BASE_ORIGIN...

      FidoNet origin for the message base. Use - if none.

@endnode

@node BASE_FIDOADD "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_FIDOADD"

BASE_FIDOADD..

      4d FidoNet address. Use - if none.

@endnode

@node BASE_ALLOWPBLC "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_ALLOWPBLC"

BASE_ALLOWPBLC

      If  this is Y, users can write public messages to this base.  If N,
      they can't.

@endnode

@node BASE_ALLOWPRIV "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_ALLOWPRIV"

BASE_ALLOWPRIV

      If  this is Y, users can write private message to this base.  If N,
      they can't.

@endnode

@node BASE_FILEATTAC "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_FILEATTAC"

BASE_FILEATTAC

      If this is Y, users can attach files to the messages they send.

@endnode

@node BASE_NAMES "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_NAMES"

BASE_NAMES....

      If  this is R, real names will be used in this base.  If this is H,
      handles will be used.

@endnode

@node BASE_ALL=EALL "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_ALL=EALL"

BASE_ALL=EALL.

        If you want that users all regular messages to all users will
        be exclusive all messages (will be shown in mailscan) set this
        as Y. 

@endnode

@node BASE_QUOTE "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_QUOTE"

BASE_QUOTE....

      Quoting  method.   If  L,  /X-like quoteline will be inserted after
      quote.   If this is >, plain > will be inserted before each line of
      the  quote.   If this is I, initials of the original message author
      and ">" will be inserted before quote. EG.  "AH> DayDream KiX a$$!"

@endnode

@node BASE_DEFGRAB "DayDream BBS - Conferences - BASE_DEFGRAB"

BASE_DEFGRAB..

      Y/N  switch.  Use Y, if  you want  this messagebase  to be turned on
      as default for new mail scan and message grabbing.

@endnode

@node ExtCommands "DayDream BBS - External Commands"

External Commands
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
DayDream  supports  5 kinds of doors.  They are DosScript (not so useful),
DDDP  (DayDream  DoorProtocol, like XIM in AmiX), stdio-doors, ARexx-doors
and  textfiles.   ARexx  interface  is  external,  program  called rexx in
Doors/-directory converts ARexx<->DDDP.

Paragon-door support is not ready yet.

To  use  any DayDream-door  you will need ENV:-variable called DreamUtils.
Doors  and  utils  should  look  for  their configfiles from path which is
placed  in  that  ENV:-variable.  This provides possiblity for you to have
configfiles placed where ever you want.  Example configfiles are placed in
DayDream:Configs/  so  type  "setenv  DreamUtils DayDream:Configs/" to get
doors  and  utils  working.   Stdio-doors/dos  programs  support following
parameters:

%N - Node
%R - Real name
%H - Handle
%S - Screenlength
%D - Device
%U - Unit
%B - Bps rate of the current connection
%L - Locked baud rate
%A - Access level
%T - Time left in minutes

DDDP and Paragon Doors only support these parameters:

%N - Node
%R - Real name
%H - Handle

More will be added if you request something.


Example configuration of an external command :

!EXTERNALCOMMANDS.DAT
@{" DOOR_COMMAND.. " Link DOOR_COMMAND} WALL
@{" DOOR_TYPE..... " Link DOOR_TYPE} 1
@{" DOOR_SECURITY. " Link DOOR_SECURITY} 5
@{" DOOR_EXECUTE.. " Link DOOR_EXECUTE} DayDream:Doors/Wall %N
@{" DOOR_CONFS1... " Link DOOR_CONFS1} XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
@{" DOOR_CONFS2... " Link DOOR_CONFS2} XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
+

  The  next line specifies what to do next.  If it's +, then there's another
  door to compile.  If it's ~, it's the end of the ExternalCommands.DAT.

@endnode

@node DOOR_COMMAND "DayDream BBS - External Commands - DOOR_COMMAND"

DOOR_COMMAND.. 

      Command at main prompt to launch this door.

@endnode

@node DOOR_TYPE "DayDream BBS - External Commands - DOOR_TYPE"

DOOR_TYPE..... 

      Door type. 0 = Dos program  without any  kind of output or  input to
                     the serial or console.

                 1 = DDDP  door  (DayDream Door  Protocol).  DDDP  is very
                     flexible method for programming doors. Specifications
                     of DDDP are included in Developer/-directory.

                 2 = Paragon  door.   Tuomas  wrote  this,  but  it's  not
                     finished yet. I don't have specifications for Paragon
                     doors, so  I've been  unable  to finish  writing this
                     ready, sorry.

                 3 = Stdio door.  Uses  Matthew Dillon's  fifo.library and
                     fifo-handler. Standard dos programs  which won't open
                     screen or window will work.

                 4 = Text file.  Specified  text file from current display
                     directory  will  be  shown  to the  user.  Useful for
                     doormenus etc.
               
                 5 = Internal command. Allows  you  to change commands  of
                     the main menu.

@endnode

@node DOOR_SECURITY "DayDream BBS - External Commands - DOOR_SECURITY"

DOOR_SECURITY. 

      Security level required to run this door.

@endnode

@node DOOR_EXECUTE "DayDream BBS - External Commands - DOOR_EXECUTE"

DOOR_EXECUTE.. 

      Command or filename to run the door. %N required for all DDDP doors.
      - to disable command (if doortype = 5).

@endnode

@node DOOR_CONFS1 "DayDream BBS - External Commands - DOORS_CONFS1"

DOOR_CONFS1..

      Flags for conferences 1-32. If X, door is available in conf, if -
      then it's not.

@endnode 

@node DOOR_CONFS2 "DayDream BBS - External Commands - DOORS_CONFS2"

DOOR_CONFS2..

      Flags for conferences 32-64. If X, door is available in conf, if -
      then it's not.

@endnode 

@node AccPresets "DayDream BBS - Access Presets"

Access Presets
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{" PRESET_SEC.... " Link PRESET_SEC} 5
@{" PRESET_NUMBER. " Link PRESET_NUMBER} 1
@{" PRESET_FFILES. " Link PRESET_FFILES} 0
@{" PRESET_FBYTES. " Link PRESET_FBYTES} 0
@{" PRESET_DESC... " Link PRESET_DESC} New User
@{" PRESET_STATUS. " Link PRESET_STATUS} 3
+

The  next  line specifies what to do next.  If it's +, then there's preset
to compile.  If it's ~, it's the end of the Access.DAT.

@endnode

@node PRESET_SEC "DayDream BBS - Access Presets - PRESET_SEC"

PRESET_SEC....

      Security level of this preset.

@endnode

@node PRESET_NUMBER "DayDream BBS - Access Presets - PRESET_NUMBER"

PRESET_NUMBER.

      Number of preset.

@endnode

@node PRESET_FFILES "DayDream BBS - Access Presets - PRESET_FFILES"

PRESET_FFILES.

      Free files.

@endnode

@node PRESET_FBYTES "DayDream BBS - Access Presets - PRESET_FBYTES"

PRESET_FBYTES.

      Free bytes. (In KB!!!)

@endnode

@node PRESET_DESC "DayDream BBS - Access Presets - PRESET_DESC"

PRESET_DESC...

      Description of the preset.

@endnode

@node PRESET_STATUS "DayDream BBS - Access Presets - PRESET_STATUS"

PRESET_STATUS.

      Status of the preset. 0 = Active, 1 = Deleted, 2 = Frozen, 3 = New

@endnode

@node Archivers "DayDream BBS - Archivers"

Archivers
~~~~~~~~~
!ARCHIVERS.DAT
@{" ARC_TYPE...... " Link ARC_TYPE} F
@{" ARC_EXTENSION. " Link ARC_EXTENSION} LHA
@{" ARC_NAME...... " Link ARC_NAME} LHA
@{" ARC_TEST...... " Link ARC_TEST} dh1:utils/lha -m -M T %A
@{" ARC_FAIL1..... " Link ARC_FAIL1} Failed
@{" ARC_FAIL2..... " Link ARC_FAIL2} -
@{" ARC_FAIL3..... " Link ARC_FAIL3} -
@{" ARC_FIDEXTRACT " Link ARC_FIDEXTRACT} dh1:utils/lha -m -M E %A %F
@{" ARC_FIDADD.... " Link ARC_FIDADD} dh1:utils/lha -m -M A %A %F
@{" ARC_VIEW...... " Link ARC_VIEW} dh1:utils/lha L %A %F
@{" ARC_OFFLINE... " Link ARC_OFFLINE} Y
@{" ARC_GETDATE... " Link ARC_GETDATE} Y
@{" ARC_DELETECOR. " Link ARC_DELETECOR} Y
@{" ARC_DISPLAY... " Link ARC_DISPLAY} Y
@{" ARC_SECVIEW... " Link ARC_SECVIEW} 200
+

The next line specifies what to do next.  If it's +, then there's archiver
to compile.  If it's ~, it's the end of the Archivers.DAT.

@endnode

@node ARC_TYPE "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_TYPE"

ARC_TYPE......

      Archiver type. F = File archiver, D = Disk archiver.

@endnode

@node ARC_EXTENSION "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_EXTENSION"

ARC_EXTENSION.

      Extension of the archive.

@endnode

@node ARC_NAME "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_NAME"

ARC_NAME......

      Archiver name.

@endnode

@node ARC_TEST "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_TEST"

ARC_TEST......

      Test command of the archiver (- for none)

@endnode

@node ARC_FAIL1 "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_FAIL1"

ARC_FAIL1.....

      Keyword if archive is corrupted (- for none). Case-sensitive. 

@endnode

@node ARC_FAIL2 "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_FAIL2"

ARC_FAIL2.....

      Keyword if archive is corrupted (- for none). Case-sensitive. 

@endnode

@node ARC_FAIL3 "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_FAIL3"

ARC_FAIL3.....

      Keyword if archive is corrupted (- for none). Case-sensitive. 

@endnode

@node ARC_FIDEXTRACT "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_FIDEXTRACT"

ARC_FIDEXTRACT

      File_id.diz extract command (- for none)

@endnode

@node ARC_VIEW "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_VIEW"

ARC_VIEW

      Archive view command (- for none)

@endnode

@node ARC_FIDADD "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_FIDADD"

ARC_FIDADD....

      File_id.diz add command (- for none)

@endnode

@node ARC_OFFLINE "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_OFFLINE"

ARC_OFFLINE... 

      Use offline checking to check the files. (Y/N)

@endnode

@node ARC_GETDATE "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_GETDATE"

ARC_GETDATE... 

      Get  date  from  file_id.diz  and insert it to the filedescription.
      Note that using this isn't wise for textfiles.  (Y/N)

@endnode

@node ARC_DELETECOR "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_DELETECOR"

ARC_DELETECOR. 

      Delete file if it is corrupt. (Y/N)

@endnode

@node ARC_DISPLAY "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_DISPLAY"

ARC_DISPLAY...

      Display testing output the the user. (Y/N). Requires FIFO:.

@endnode

@node ARC_SECVIEW "DayDream BBS - Archivers - ARC_SECVIEW"

ARC_SECVIEW...

      Minimum security level to view file.

@endnode

@node Protocols "DayDream BBS - File Transfer Protocols"

File transfer protocols
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
DayDream   uses  external  xpr-protocols  for  transfering  files.   Hydra
protocol  routines and configurations are hard coded, so you don't need to
care about Hydra.

!PROTOCOLS.DAT
@{" XPR_ID........ " Link XPR_ID} Z
@{" XPR_NAME...... " Link XPR_NAME} Z-Modem
@{" XPR_EFFICIENCY " Link XPR_EFFICIENCY} 97
@{" XPR_LIB....... " Link XPR_LIB} xprzmodem.library
@{" XPR_INIT...... " Link XPR_INIT} TN,OR,B10,DN,KY,SN,RN
@{" XPR_TYPE...... " Link XPR_TYPE} X
~

The next line specifies what to do next.  If it's +, then there's protocol
to compile.  If it's ~, it's the end of the Protocols.DAT.

@endnode

@node XPR_ID "DayDream BBS - File Transfer Protocols - XPR_ID"

XPR_ID........ 

      Protocol ID for Alter userdata menu.

@endnode

@node XPR_NAME "DayDream BBS - File Transfer Protocols - XPR_NAME"

XPR_NAME...... 

      Protocol name.

@endnode

@node XPR_EFFICIENCY "DayDream BBS - File Transfer Protocols - XPR_EFFICIENCY"

XPR_EFFICIENCY 

      Protocol efficiency in percents.

@endnode

@node XPR_LIB "DayDream BBS - File Transfer Protocols - XPR_LIB"

XPR_LIB....... 

      XPR-library name. (Or -)

@endnode

@node XPR_INIT "DayDream BBS - File Transfer Protocols - XPR_INIT"

XPR_INIT...... 

      XPR init string. Refer to library's doc for more info.

@endnode

@node XPR_TYPE "DayDream BBS - File Transfer Protocols - XPR_TYPE"

XPR_TYPE...... 

      Protocol type. X = XPR, S = Smodem, H = Hydra, F = FTP.

@endnode

@node DisplayModes "DayDream BBS - Display Modes"

Display Modes
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
!DISPLAY.DAT
@{" DPL_ID........ " Link DPL_ID} 1
@{" DPL_PATH...... " Link DPL_PATH} Iso/
@{" DPL_ANSI...... " Link DPL_ANSI} Y
@{" DPL_INCONV.... " Link DPL_INCONV} N
@{" DPL_OUTCONV... " Link DPL_OUTCONV} N
@{" DPL_FILESCONV. " Link DPL_FILESCONV} N
@{" DPL_STRIPANSI. " Link DPL_STRIPANSI} N
@{" DPL_TRYTXT.... " Link DPL_TRYTXT} N
@{" DPL_16COL..... " Link DPL_16COL} N
@{" DPL_NEWCON.... " Link DPL_NEWCON} N
@{" DPL_TABLE..... " Link DPL_TABLE1} 0
@{" DPL_TABLE..... " Link DPL_TABLE2} 0
@{" DPL_FONT...... " Link DPL_FONT} topaz.font
@{" DPL_SIZE...... " Link DPL_SIZE} 8
@{" DPL_STRINGS... " Link DPL_STRINGS} 1
~

The  next  line  specifies  what  to  do  next.   If  it's +, then there's
displaymode to compile.  If it's ~, it's the end of the DisplayModes.DAT.

@endnode

@node DPL_ID "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_ID"

DPL_ID........

      Display mode number.

@endnode

@node DPL_PATH "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_PATH"

DPL_PATH......

      Path used by display mode to find menus and text files.  If this is
      "Iso/",        text        stuff       is       searched       from
      DayDream:Display/Iso/-directory.

@endnode

@node DPL_ANSI "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_ANSI"

DPL_ANSI......

      If this is Y, ansi colors are enabled.  If this is N, only 2 colors
      are used.

@endnode

@node DPL_INCONV "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_INCONV"

DPL_INCONV....

      Activate  incoming  conversion.   If this is Y, incoming characters
      will be converted.

@endnode

@node DPL_OUTCONV "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_OUTCONV"

DPL_OUTCONV...

      Activate  outgoing  conversion.   If this is Y, outgoing characters
      will be converted.

@endnode

@node DPL_FILESCONV "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_FILESCONV"

DPL_FILESCONV.

      Activate  textfile  conversion.   If  this is Y, outgoing textfiles
      will be converted.

@endnode

@node DPL_STRIPANSI "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_STRIPANSI"

DPL_STRIPANSI.

      Strip ansicodes from textfiles.

@endnode

@node DPL_TRYTXT "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_TRYTXT"

DPL_TRYTXT....

      If GFX file doesn't found, try TXT.

@endnode

@node DPL_16COL "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_16COL"

DPL_16COL.....

       Use 16 colors on local console. NEWCON *MUST* be enabled too.

@endnode

@node DPL_NEWCON "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_NEWCON"

DPL_NEWCON....

       Use kalacon.device for output. Kalacon is a console.device
       replacement. It supports 16 colors (EGA emulation) and
       red/white work 100%. However, it misses some console.device
       features.

@endnode

@node DPL_TABLE1 "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_TABLE1"

DPL_TABLE1....

      ID of ConversionTableXX.DAT used for incoming conversion.

@endnode

@node DPL_TABLE2 "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_TABLE2"

DPL_TABLE2....

      ID of ConversionTableXX.DAT used for outgoing conversion.

@endnode

@node DPL_FONT "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_FONT"

DPL_FONT......

      Local font when user is using this displaymode.

@endnode

@node DPL_SIZE "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_SIZE"

DPL_SIZE......

      Size of font when user is using this displaymode.

@endnode

@node DPL_STRINGS "DayDream BBS - Display Modes - DPL_STRINGS"

DPL_STRINGS...

      Number of strings to use.

@endnode

@node Multinode "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff"

Multinode stuff
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{" MNODE_NODE.... " Link MNODE_NODE} 1
@{" MNODE_IODEV... " Link MNODE_IODEV} 1
@{" MNODE_MBAUD... " Link MNODE_MBAUD} 1200
@{" MNODE_MNBAUD.. " Link MNODE_MNBAUD} 1200
@{" MNODE_FONT.... " Link MNODE_FONT} topaz.font
@{" MNODE_FSIZE... " Link MNODE_FSIZE} 8
@{" MNODE_STYPE... " Link MNODE_STYPE} 1
@{" MNODE_SHANGHAI " Link MNODE_SHANGHAI} N
@{" MNODE_DEFPTOF. " Link MNODE_DEFPTOF} N
@{" MNODE_AUTOFRNT " Link MNODE_AUTOFRNT} Y
@{" MNODE_AUTOOPEN " Link MNODE_AUTOOPEN} Y
@{" MNODE_FIXRED.. " Link MNODE_FIXRED} N
@{" MNODE_OWNDIR.. " Link MNODE_OWNDIR} N
@{" MNODE_TELNET.. " Link MNODE_TELNET} N
@{" MNODE_16COL... " Link MNODE_16COL} N
@{" MNODE_NOTIFY.. " Link MNODE_NOTIFY} Y
@{" MNODE_HIDEINAC " Link MNODE_HIDEINAC} N
@{" MNODE_HIDEWAIT " Link MNODE_HIDEWAIT} N
@{" MNODE_HIDECALL " Link MNODE_HIDECALL} N
@{" MNODE_NOPASSWD " Link MNODE_NOPASSWD} N
@{" MNODE_NEWCON.. " Link MNODE_NEWCON} N
@{" MNODE_COMMAND. " Link MNODE_COMMAND} run daydream n1 <>NIL:
@{" MNODE_PRIORITY " Link MNODE_PRIORITY} 2
@{" MNODE_TEMPDIR. " Link MNODE_TEMPDIR} DayDream:Temporary/Node1/
@{" MNODE_PENS.... " Link MNODE_PENS} 141146105414
@{" MNODE_SPEEDUP. " Link MNODE_SPEEDUP} N
+

  The  next  line  specifies  what to do next.  If it's +, then there's more
  nodes to compile.  If it's ~, it's the end of the Multinode.DAT.

@endnode

@node MNODE_NODE "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_NODE"

MNODE_NODE....

      Node number of this node. DO NOT USE 0!

@endnode

@node MNODE_IODEV "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_IODEV"

MNODE_IODEV...

      Number of IO-Device to use.

@endnode

@node MNODE_MBAUD "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_MBAUD"

MNODE_MBAUD...

      Minimum baud to allow logon.

@endnode

@node MNODE_MNBAUD "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_MNBAUD"

MNODE_MNBAUD..

      Minimum baud to allow new users to logon.

@endnode

@node MNODE_FONT "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_FONT"

MNODE_FONT....

      Font to use for this node.

@endnode

@node MNODE_FSIZE "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_FSIZE"

MNODE_FSIZE...

      Font size for this node.

@endnode

@node MNODE_STYPE "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_STYPE"

MNODE_STYPE...

      Screen  type  for this node.  0 = Custom screen, 1 = Public Screen.
      If  you  want  that  Hydra  will  open it's windows to the DayDream
      screen, you had better use public screen.

@endnode

@node MNODE_SHANGHAI "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_SHANGHAI"

MNODE_SHANGHAI

      Shanghai windows.

@endnode

@node MNODE_DEFPTOF "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_DEFPTOF"

MNODE_DEFPTOF.

      Default public screen to front when visitor.

@endnode

@node MNODE_AUTOFRNT "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_AUTOFRNT"

MNODE_AUTOFRNT

      Screen to front when connected.

@endnode

@node MNODE_AUTOOPEN "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_AUTOOPEN"

MNODE_AUTOOPEN

      Open  screen  when  node  starts (Not yet available, screen will be
      opened always)

@endnode

@node MNODE_FIXRED "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_FIXRED"

MNODE_FIXRED

      Fix red/white "distortion". Ansicode 37m  should display white  and
      it does,  if this  is turned on. This  is a little "bug" in Amiga's
      console.device and if you use this option, console output will be a
      bit slower. I advice you to turn this on only on local nodes.
      NOTE! Requires V39 OS.

@endnode

@node MNODE_OWNDIR "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_OWNDIR"

MNODE_OWNDIR..

      Get Display stuff  from  DayDream:Node[number]/Display/  instead of
      DayDream:Display/.

@endnode

@node MNODE_16COL "DayDream BBS - Multinode - MNODE_16COL"

MNODE_16COL.....

       Use 16 colors on local console. NEWCON *MUST* be enabled too.

@endnode


@node MNODE_TELNET "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_TELNET"

MNODE_TELNET..

      If this is Y, DD expects that the node is TELNET node. BPS rate
      will be same as DTE and WHO shows that node is TELNET node.

@endnode

@node MNODE_NOTIFY "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_NOTIFY"

MNODE_NOTIFY..

      If this is Y, other nodes will be informed on logins/logouts.

@endnode

@node MNODE_HIDEINAC "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_HIDEINAC"

      If this is Y, node will be hidden when inactive.

@endnode

@node MNODE_HIDEWAIT "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_HIDEWAIT"

      If this is Y, node will be hidden when waiting for call.

@endnode

@node MNODE_HIDECALL "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_HIDECALL"

      If this is Y, node will be hidden when there's caller online.

@endnode

@node MNODE_NOPASSWD "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_NOPASSWD"

      If this is Y, node will skip System/User passwords.

@endnode

@node MNODE_NEWCON "DayDream BBS - Multinode - MNODE_NEWCON"

MNODE_NEWCON..

       Use kalacon.device for output. Kalacon is a console.device
       replacement. It supports 16 colors (EGA emulation) and
       red/white work 100%. However, it misses some console.device
       features.

@endnode


@node MNODE_COMMAND "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_COMMAND"

MNODE_COMMAND.

      Command to run when node is inactive and clicked from server.

@endnode

@node MNODE_PRIORITY "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_PRIORITY"

MNODE_PRIORITY

      Priority for node.

@endnode

@node MNODE_TEMPDIR "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_TEMPDIR"

MNODE_TEMPDIR.

      Path to place uploads while they are being received to the system.

@endnode

@node MNODE_PENS "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_PENS"

MNODE_PENS....

      This allows you to edit screen pens. You can adjust the pen that
      is used to draw borders etc in local DD screen.

      Colors are like this:

                             0 = BLACK
                             1 = WHITE (RED if FIXRED is on)
                             2 = GREEN
                             3 = YELLOW
                             4 = BLUE
                             5 = MAGENTA
                             6 = CYAN
                             7 = RED (WHITE if FIXRED is on)

      Screen looks very good if fixred is off and pens are
      141146105414 or if fixred is on and pens are 747746705474.

      Try some combinations to get the idea :)

@endnode

@node MNODE_SPEEDUP "DayDream BBS - Multinode Stuff - MNODE_SPEEDUP"

MNODE_PENS....

	If set to Y, this opens a 4 colour local screen for this node.
        Use this if you want to have a speedup boost.

@endnode

@node InputOutput "DayDream BBS - I/O Devices"

I/O Devices
~~~~~~~~~~~
!IO-DEVICES.DAT
@{" IO_NUMBER..... " Link IO_NUMBER} 1
@{" IO_UNIT....... " Link IO_UNIT} 0
@{" IO_BAUD....... " Link IO_BAUD} 38400
@{" IO_DEVICE..... " Link IO_DEVICE} serial.device
@{" IO_PREINIT.... " Link IO_PREINIT} |ATZ|
@{" IO_OFFHOOK.... " Link IO_OFFHOOK} AT &D0 M0 H1|
@{" IO_ANSWER..... " Link IO_ANSWER} ATA|
@{" IO_INIT....... " Link IO_INIT} AT M0 L0W2%C3\A3\N3\L1|
@{" IO_AFTERCALL.. " Link IO_AFTERCALL} AT&D2 ATH0|
@{" IO_OK......... " Link IO_OK} OK
@{" IO_RING....... " Link IO_RING} RING
@{" IO_NOCARRIER.. " Link IO_NOCARRIER} NO CARRIER
@{" IO_CONNECT.... " Link IO_CONNECT} CONNECT
@{" IO_SPEED1..... " Link IO_SPEED1} HST,14400
@{" IO_SPEED2..... " Link IO_SPEED2} -
@{" IO_SPEED3..... " Link IO_SPEED3} -
@{" IO_SPEED4..... " Link IO_SPEED4} -
@{" IO_SPEED5..... " Link IO_SPEED5} -
@{" IO_SPEED6..... " Link IO_SPEED6} -
@{" IO_SPEED7..... " Link IO_SPEED7} -
@{" IO_SPEED8..... " Link IO_SPEED8} -
@{" IO_SPEED9..... " Link IO_SPEED9} -
@{" IO_SPEED10.... " Link IO_SPEED10} -
@{" IO_ERRORCORR.. " Link IO_ERRORCORR} ARQ
@{" IO_DELAY1..... " Link IO_DELAY1} 1
@{" IO_DELAY2..... " Link IO_DELAY2} 2
@{" IO_MODE....... " Link IO_MODE} S
~

The  next  line  specifies  what to do next.  If it's +, then there's more
IO-Devices to compile.  If it's ~, it's the end of the IO-Devices.

@endnode

