@node Schedule "DayDream BBS - Schedule"

Schedule
~~~~~~~~
!SCHEDULE.DAT
@{" SCHE_HOUR..... " Link SCHE_HOUR} 0
@{" SCHE_LOGOFF... " Link SCHE_LOGOFF} N
@{" SCHE_SYSPW.... " Link SCHE_SYSPW} -
@{" SCHE_NEWUSERPW " Link SCHE_NEWUSERPW} -
+

  The  next  line specifies what to do next.  If it's +, then there's more
  hours to compile.  If it's ~, it's the end of the Schedule.DAT.  Note that
  you MUST have all 24 hours in this block!

@endnode

@node SCHE_HOUR "DayDream BBS - Schedule - SCHE_HOUR"

SCHE_HOUR..... 

      Hour. 0-23. 

@endnode

@node SCHE_LOGOFF "DayDream BBS - Schedule - SCHE_LOGOFF"

SCHE_LOGOFF... 

      Force logoff at the end of this hour.

@endnode

@node SCHE_SYSPW "DayDream BBS - Schedule - SCHE_SYSPW"

SCHE_SYSPW.... 

      System password at this hour (- for none)

@endnode

@node SCHE_NEWUSERPW "DayDream BBS - Schedule - SCHE_NEWUSERPW"

  SCHE_NEWUSERPW 

        New user password at this hour (- for none)

@endnode

