@node SREXX1 "Server Arexx Commands - SHUTDOWN"

SHUTDOWN - Close DD Server. Works only if all nodes have been closed first.

examle:
SHUTDOWN

@endnode

@node SREXX2 "Server Arexx Commands - ICONIFY"

ICONIFY - Iconifies the server.

example:
ICONIFY

@endnode

@node SREXX3 "Server Arexx Commands - CLOSENODE"

CLOSENODE [node] - Close the specified node. Closes even if there's
                   user online. Use NODEINFO first if you don't want
                   to kick someone out.

Example:
CLOSENODE 1

@endnode

@node SREXX4 "Server Arexx Commands - OPENSCREEN"

OPENSCREEN [node] - Open the screen of the specified node.

Example:
OPENSCREEN 1

@endnode

@node SREXX5 "Server Arexx Commands - CLOSESCREEN"

CLOSESCREEN [node] - Close the screen of the specified node.

Example:
CLOSESCREEN 1

@endnode

@node SREXX6 "Server Arexx Commands - KICKUSER"

KICKUSER [node] - Disconnect user from the specified node.

Example:
KICKUSER 1

@endnode

@node SREXX7 "Server Arexx Commands - ENTERCHAT"

ENTERCHAT [node] - Activate chat mode on the specified node.

Example:
ENTERCHAT 1

@endnode

@node SREXX8 "Server Arexx Commands - CHATON"

CHATON - Turn SysOp abailable flag on. 

Example:
CHATON

@endnode

@node SREXX9 "Server Arexx Commands - CHATOFF"

CHATOFF [reason] - Turn off SysOp available flag. Requires a reason.

Example:
CHATOFF "Shut up, I'm hunting wabbits.."

@endnode

@node SREXXA "Server Arexx Commands - NODEINFO"

NODEINFO [node] [cmd] - Get info on node.

Get information about a specified node.

cmd can be on of:
    0 = Returns information wheter Node is active(1) or not(0).
    1 = Returns information wheter there is a user online(1) or not(0).
    2 = Returns user activity string
    3 = Returns user handle
    4 = Returns user realname
    5 = Returns user location
    6 = Returns user organization

Example:
NODEINFO 1 0

@endnode

@node SREXXE "Server ARexx Examples"
/* Testing Server ARexx... */

Options results
servid="SERVER-REXX"
address value servid

iconify
chatoff "I'm not available right now, sorry."

exit

More example scripts can be found in the DayDream:Rexx/ drawer.

@endnode


@node ExamineDInfo "Developer information about Examine.DAT/FileCheck.DAT"

Filename is  passed to door in DD's  commandline parameters. Do NOT  trash
it, since  there  can be more  doors  in Examine.DAT  to be launched.  The
current directory is temporary directory where  uploads are placed, so you
don't need to do any CurrentDir()s or generate path to find the file.


Here's a VERY simple example written in ARexx:

--------------------------------------------------------------cut---------
/* Introducing Examine.DAT */

parse arg node
Options results
nodeid="DREAMREXX"node
address value nodeid

systeminfo 3
file = result
transmit "[36mThank you for uploading [0m"file"[36m!"
if file = "RYLDD110.LHA" then call deleteit
call awaywego
deleteit:
address command "delete "file
transmit '[0mOnly nerds upload such crap!'

awaywego:
transmit '[0m'
shutdown
exit
--------------------------------------------------------------cut---------

@endnode
@node HowDoesItWork "DayDream BBS - How Does It Work"

                             How does it work

                              @{" General Info    " Link work1}
                              @{" Login Procedure " Link work2}
                              @{" User Commands   " Link work3}
                              @{" SysOp Commands  " Link work4}

                              @{" Back To Main    " Link Main}

